{"parse":{"title":"All-Russian Teachers' Union","pageid":37029835,"revid":700201501,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>All-Russian Teachers' Union</b> (<i>Vserossiiskii soiuz uchitelei</i>, or VUS<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>) was a <a href=\"/wiki/Trade_union\" title=\"Trade union\">trade union</a> for teachers founded in the 1890s<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and active during the <a href=\"/wiki/Russian_Revolution\" title=\"Russian Revolution\">Russian revolutions</a> of 1917. It was dissolved in December 1918 following conflict with the <a href=\"/wiki/Bolsheviks\" title=\"Bolsheviks\">Bolsheviks</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Conflict_with_Bolsheviks\">Conflict with Bolsheviks</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=All-Russian_Teachers%27_Union&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Conflict with Bolsheviks\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>After the Bolshevik seizure of power in the <a href=\"/wiki/October_Revolution\" title=\"October Revolution\">October Revolution</a>, the VUS went on strike along with officials of the <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_Education\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ministry of Education\">Ministry of Education</a> and the State Education Committee. The <a href=\"/wiki/Petrograd\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Petrograd\">Petrograd</a> branch of the VUS resolved \"not to perform the instructions of the self-styled power.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Fitzpatrick_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Fitzpatrick-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> They stayed out on strike until 6 January 1918. The <a href=\"/wiki/Moscow\" title=\"Moscow\">Moscow</a> branch, with around 4000 members, joined the strike of municipal workers, and remained on strike until 11 March 1918.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Fitzpatrick_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Fitzpatrick-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The Bolsheviks claimed that the VUS was receiving financial backing from <a href=\"/wiki/Pavel_Ryabushinsky\" title=\"Pavel Ryabushinsky\">Pavel Ryabushinsky</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Anatoly_Lunacharsky\" title=\"Anatoly Lunacharsky\">Anatoly Lunacharsky</a> commented in <i>Petrogradskii uchitel</i>:\n</p>\n<dl><dd>'We are obliged to dismiss <i>for ever</i> from school activity these honourable gentlemen who, in spite of our appeal, prefer to continue in the role of political matadors rather than the role of teachers.</dd>\n<dd>'I do not know what quantity of repentant tears the individual teachers may, in the eyes of the people, wash away the black letters which he himself has painted on his forehead: <i>\"In December 1917, in the hour of the people's terrible struggle against the exploiters, I refused to teach the children and received money for this from the exploiters' funds.\"</i></dd></dl>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-Fitzpatrick_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Fitzpatrick-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=All-Russian_Teachers%27_Union&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Seregny, Scott Joseph (1989). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=dUZFF99kSx4C&amp;pg=PA115\"><i>Russian Teachers and Peasant Revolution: The Politics of Education in 1905</i></a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Indiana_University_Press\" title=\"Indiana University Press\">Indiana University Press</a>. p.&#160;115<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">17 July</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Russian+Teachers+and+Peasant+Revolution%3A+The+Politics+of+Education+in+1905&amp;rft.pages=115&amp;rft.pub=Indiana+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1989&amp;rft.aulast=Seregny&amp;rft.aufirst=Scott+Joseph&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DdUZFF99kSx4C%26pg%3DPA115&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAll-Russian+Teachers%27+Union\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://history.columbusstate.edu/newsletters/05_06Newsletter.pdf\">\"Faculty News\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. <i>Department of History and Geography</i>. Columbus State University. February 2007. p.&#160;3<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">September 16,</span> 2012</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Department+of+History+and+Geography&amp;rft.atitle=Faculty+News&amp;rft.pages=3&amp;rft.date=2007-02&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fhistory.columbusstate.edu%2Fnewsletters%2F05_06Newsletter.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAll-Russian+Teachers%27+Union\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Fitzpatrick-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Fitzpatrick_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Fitzpatrick_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b